##  What   changes

5
00:00:16.010 --> 00:00:19.880
  for   the   creator  <break time="800ms" />

 They   paste   the   whole   script   once

6
00:00:19.880 --> 00:00:23.390
.  They   choose   a   voice .  They   press   generate ,  then   they

7
00:00:23.390 --> 00:00:27.960
  get   final   audio   and   subtitle-ready   timing   without   manual   chunking

8
00:00:27.960 --> 00:00:31.320
.  <break time="600ms" /> 

-  First ,  the   system   checks   whether   the   script   is

9
00:00:31.320 --> 00:00:35.080
  readable .  <break time="350ms" /> 
-  Next ,  it   keeps   the   original   words   intact

10
00:00:35.080 --> 00:00:39.130
.  <break time="350ms" /> 
-  Then ,  it   adds   only   structural   pauses   between   sections

11
00:00:39.130 --> 00:00:42.530
.  <break time="350ms" /> 
-  Finally ,  it   records   evidence   so   a   reviewer   can

12
00:00:42.530 --> 00:00:46.470
